ZH: 我们决定雇一位新的员工。
EN: We decided to hire a new employee.

ZH: 他找到一家大公司雇他为经理。
EN: He found a big company to hire him as a manager.

ZH: 我们需要雇一名会计师来管理我们的财务。
EN: We need to hire an accountant to manage our finances.

ZH: 他在这家公司已经被雇多年了。
EN: He has been employed by this company for many years.

ZH: 雇主提供了一份有吸引力的工资薪水。
EN: The employer offered an attractive salary.

ZH: 这份工作有很好的雇佣福利。
EN: This job has excellent employment benefits.

ZH: 我们向公众征求意见以雇用一名新的市长。
EN: We seek public opinion to employ a new mayor.

ZH: 公司决定雇用四名实习生。
EN: The company decides to employ four interns.

ZH: 他建议我向这家退伍军人雇佣服务中心询问帮助。
EN: He suggested that I inquire for assistance at this veteran employment center.

ZH: 我们下个月计划雇用一名新的销售代表。
EN: We plan to hire a new sales representative next month.

ZH: 这家企业正在雇用新人。
EN: This company is currently hiring.

ZH: 该农场雇了两个人帮忙收割庄稼。
EN: The farm employed two workers to help with the harvest.

ZH: 他们是这个地区最大的雇佣主。
EN: They are the largest employer in this region.

ZH: 公司正在寻找有经验的人才来雇佣。
EN: The company is looking for experienced talent to employ.

ZH: 雇主需要确定最佳的候选人来填补这个职位。
EN: The employer needs to identify the best candidate to fill this position.

ZH: 我们期待雇人的筛选过程能找到合适的人选。
EN: We expect the hiring process to find suitable candidates.

ZH: 学校计划在下个学期雇用两名新老师。
EN: The school plans to hire two new teachers next semester.

ZH: 她已与这家公司签订了一份雇佣合同。
EN: She has signed an employment contract with this company.

ZH: 我希望能够雇用一名有才华的设计师。
EN: I hope to employ a talented designer.

ZH: 雇主要求所有申请者提交一份个人简历。
EN: The employer requests all applicants to submit a personal resume.
